":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":31,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Isabella Montacute was born in 1193, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Montacute, was 21 and her mother, Isabella Montague, was 13. She married Geoffry de Pridyas in 1218. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1226, in Cornwall, England, at the age of 33."},"et":{"1193–1226":"1193–1226","1199–1243":"1199–1243","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1222–Male":"1222–Surnud","1224–1302":"1224–1302","1172–1247":"1172–1247","1180–1226":"1180–1226","1220":"1220","1195":"1195","1172":"1172","1193":"1193","1180":"1180","1226":"1226","1215":"1215","1247":"1247","1302":"1302","1224":"1224","Abt 1199":"1199","1222":"1222","1243":"1243","1199":"1199","about 1222":"umbes 1222","about 1220":"umbes 1220","1218":"1218","Orcharton, Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom",", Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Orcharton, Adeston, Devon, England":"Devon, England","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Montague, Somerset, England":"Sutton Montis, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Gidleigh, Devon, England":"Gidleigh, Devon, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Orchaesron Manor, Modbury, Devon, England":"Modbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom